 Joel Wilkinson has a muscle wasting disease meaning he will eventually be left in a wheelchair and his life will be cut short .
The three-year-old was diagnosed with Duchenne Muscular Dystrophy just six months ago after his parents noticed he was struggling to develop and learn to walk .
They were left devastated when tests confirmed their son had the incurable condition and that his muscles will slowly waste away .
His sister Phoebe , five , adores him and has a life expectancy of just 20 .